data.meta_description: Traces of Indiana and Midwestern History is a quarterly history magazine published by the Indiana Historical Society. This issue features the articles Editors' Page: Twenty Years and Counting; The Girl from the Wabash: Louise Dresser; Gifts of the Gamboliers: Modern Art in Indianapolis; It All Started with the Donuts: From Red Skelton: The Mask Behind the Mask; Black History News and Notes: Bloody Bananas; Everyday People: Elijah Roberts; The Relic of a Barbarous Age; "The True Spirit of American Art": The Society of Western Artists; I Remember When: Genet and Me; and Images of Indiana.
